Three criminals removed the horn shark, named 'Miss Helen', from its tank and smuggled it out by disguising it as a baby in a pushchair. JOHANNESBURG - Police in Texas are questioning suspects who allegedly stole a shark from an aquarium. Three criminals removed the horn shark, named "Miss Helen", from its tank and smuggled it out by disguising it as a baby in a pushchair. Miss Helen was safely recovered shortly after CCTV footage of the abduction was released. She's been taken back to the aquarium. WATCH: Shark stolen from San Antonio Aquarium 